<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>With just under two weeks until the international transfer window closes on October 5, clubs across Europe are looking to bring in flesh blood as the 2020-21 season starts to get going.  </p>

<p>Sportsmail provides live transfer window updates from the Premier League and clubs across Europe including permanent signings, loan deals and latest negotiations. </p>

<p>Host commentator</p>

<p>Frank Lampard believes the club's £22million move for Rennes' goalkeeper Edouard Mendy is on the verge of completion.</p>

<p>The Chelsea boss has been trying to bring in a new shot-stopper all summer and looks to finally have his man.</p>

<p>Manchester United are trying to drive down Porto's £17million price for left back Alex Telles.</p>

<p>The 27-year-old is out of contract next summer and the clubs remain apart in valuation. United are awaiting a revised bid from Roma for defender Chris Smalling who has made it clear he wishes to leave. United rejected the last offer of around £12m.</p>

<p>And welcome to Sportsmail's live transfer blog, as the window sets to wind down to a conclusion in the coming weeks!</p>

<p>Stay tuned for all the latest updates as they happen!</p>
